This is the second level overlay that can be reached when the user selects a line item under Active Recipients on the
Recipient Landing overlay. This screen provides more detailed information pertaining to the recipient and lists all the
accounts associated with this recipient. The main actions that can be taken on this page are view payment history, make a
payment, and edit recipient details. Additionally, the user may change the status on a recipient by suspending or deleting
them - actions that may require authorization.
Here, user may chose to ‘Suspend’ of ‘Delete’ a recipient. These actions may require addition authorizations to
complete. Clicking on each text link will prompt the appropriate task flow accordingly.
Selecting Suspend Recipient will prompt a task flow, allowing the user to add a comment and confirm their action to
suspend. The status of the Recipient will be changed to “Suspended” and the suspend recipient text link will change
Selecting Delete Recipient will prompt a task flow, allowing the user to add a comment and confirm their action to
delete. After deleting a recipient, the recipient will no longer appear on the Recipient Landing page for OU users,
allowing only DBank employees to view the deleted recipient. With this, OU users can find related payment history
for the deleted recipient within the Payments Landing page, if payments have been created for the recipient. Since
deleted recipients cannot be viewed by OU users, only DBank employees will be able to view the optional comment
made by the user that deleted the recipient through the Activity Log table.
The selection of the edit icon here will prompt the edit recipient information flow starting with the ‘Edit Recipient
Information’ screen which allows the user to make changes to the basic information and address of the recipient.
This action may require authorization to complete.
The selection of the edit icon here will prompt the edit account information flow starting with the ‘Edit Account
Information’ screen which allows the user to make changes or add to the account information of the recipient. This
action may require authorization to complete.
The final section on this page is the Activity Log of the recipient. This section provides a view into the different
actions that have been made to the recipient, giving insight into creation, editing, approval, and suspension process
of a recipient. Here users will be able to see when recipient has been created, edited, approved, sent back,
suspended, reactivated, and who committed each actions. Authorizers are also able to leave comments during the
approval process of a recipient, as to provide additional detail into the action they took.
The selection of ‘View Payment History’ CTA will take user to the Recipient Payment History overlay where they can
see all the past payments of this recipient.
Selection of ‘Make Payment’ CTA takes user to the enter payment screen to start the flow for payment creation of a
Since this is the overlay experience, the ‘x’ icon will still be visible for users to action on. If the user clicks on the ‘x’
icon then it would be essentially like clicking on the icon on Recipient Landing page (first level overlay) which will
take the user back to the Payment Landing page.
The back button is to indicate that the user can go back to the previous step in the overlay experience, which in this
case, is the Recipient Landing overlay.
